W0105070504: GASTROINTESTINAL INFECTIONS - MULTIPLEX NA REAGENTS
Additional Product description:
For in vitro diagnostic use. The EntericBio® Gastro Panel 2 assay is a semi-automated, two-strip molecular diagnostic test for the direct, qualitative detection of nucleic acids from Salmonella enterica spp., Shigella spp., Campylobacter jejuni / coli / lari, Shiga-like toxin-producing E. coli (STEC, also known as Verotoxin-producing E. coli, VTEC), Cryptosporidium parvum / hominis and Giardia lamblia in human stool samples. The assay is intended for use with liquid/loose stool samples from symptomatic patients with suspected acute gastroenteritis of bacterial or parasitic origin.

The EntericBio® Gastro Panel 2 assay can be used in combination with the optional UgenTec FastFinder Software using the EntericBio® Gastro Panel 2 plug-in for the analysis and results interpretation of the EntericBio® Gastro Panel 2 assay PCR raw data results generated on the LightCycler® 480 II PCR instrument.[EN]

For in vitro diagnostic use. The EntericBio® Clostridioides difficile (C. difficile) assay is a semi-automated, one–strip molecular diagnostic test for the direct, qualitative detection of nucleic acids from Clostridioides difficile in human stool samples. The assay is intended for use with stool samples from symptomatic individuals to aid in the diagnosis of Clostridioides difficile infection.
The EntericBio® C. difficile assay can be used in combination with the optional UgenTec FastFinder software using the EntericBio® C. difficile plug-in for the analysis and results interpretation of the EntericBio® C. difficile assay PCR raw data results generated on the Roche LightCycler® 480 II PCR instrument.[EN]

Nomenclature code(s): W0104080606: NUCLEIC ACID IDENTIFICATION - MANUAL / AUTOMATED CARBAPENEMASE
Additional Product description:
For in vitro diagnostic use. The EntericBio® CPE assay is a semi-automated, molecular diagnostic test for the direct, qualitative detection of carbapenemase genes in Enterobacteriaceae from human stool specimens. The assay is intended for use with stool samples or rectal swabs (in liquid medium) as well as bacterial isolates cultured from clinical specimens to aid in the detection, identification and infection control of carbapenemase-producing Enterobacteriaceae that colonise patients in healthcare settings.
The EntericBio® CPE assay can be used in combination with the optional UgenTec FastFinder software using the EntericBio® CPE plug-in for the analysis and results interpretation of the EntericBio® CPE assay PCR raw data results generated on the Roche LightCycler® 480 II PCR instrument.[EN]

Nomenclature code(s): W0105070503: RESPIRATORY TRACT INFECTIONS - MULTIPLEX NA REAGENTS
Additional Product description:
The RespiBio® Panel 1 assay, is a molecular, in-vitro diagnostic test for qualitative detection of SARS-CoV-2 from RNA extracted from nasopharyngeal swabs (in viral transport medium) from individuals with signs and symptoms of respiratory infection.
The assay utilises automated real-time polymerase chain reaction (PCR). This test is intended for use, in conjunction with clinical presentation, laboratory findings and epidemiological information, as an aid in the diagnosis of SARS-CoV-2 (COVID-19) infection in humans.
Results of this assay should not be used as the sole basis for diagnosis, treatment, or other patient management decisions. Positive results do not rule out co-infection with other organisms that are not detected by this test and may not be the sole or definitive cause of patient illness. Negative results in the setting of clinical illness compatible with respiratory infection may be due to infection by pathogens that are not detected by this test.[EN]

Nomenclature code(s): W0105070304: INFLUENZA & PARA INFLUENZA / RESPIRATORY SYNCYTIAL VIRUS (RSV) - MULTIPLEX NA REAGENTS
Additional Product description:
For in vitro diagnostic use. The RespiBio® Panel 2 assay, is a semi-automated one-strip molecular diagnostic test for qualitative detection of RNA from Influenza A, Influenza B and RSV from human nasopharyngeal swabs (in viral transport medium) from individuals with signs and symptoms of respiratory infection in a clinical laboratory setting.
The assay utilises automated real-time polymerase chain reaction (PCR). This test is intended for use, in conjunction with clinical presentation, laboratory findings and epidemiological information, as an aid in the diagnosis of Influenza A/B and RSV infections in humans.
Results of this assay should not be used as the sole basis for diagnosis, treatment, or other patient management decisions. Positive results do not rule out co-infection with other organisms that are not detected by this test and may not be the sole or definitive cause of patient illness. Negative results in the setting of clinical illness compatible with respiratory infection may be due to infection by pathogens that are not detected by this test.[EN]

This kit is for personal use by untrained layman as a rapid test method for SARS-CoV-2 antigen detection. It is suitable for users over 15 years old. Users under 15 years of age should be tested with assistance of adult.COVID-19 is an acute infectious disease of the respiratory system caused by the infection of the SARS-CoV-2 virus.. Symptoms may appear 2-14 days after exposure to the virus. Anyone can have mild to severe symptoms. Some people even suffer critical symptoms (respiratory failure, shock, or multiorgan dysfunction, etc.). Older people are at a higher risk of developing severe symptoms. SARS-CoV-2 is a novel coronavirus in β genus, enveloped particles in round or oval, with a diameter from 60 nm to 140 nm. Human is generally susceptible to SARS-CoV-2. The main sources of infection are the confirmed COVID-19 patients and asymptomatic carriers of SARS-CoV-2. SARS-CoV-2 is detectable in specimen of oropharyngeal swab, nasopharyngeal swab, anterior nasal swab and saliva. Detection of SARS-CoV-2 antigen can provide evidence for assessing the infection situation and aiding clinical diagnosis of COVID-19.[EN]
Critical warnings or contra-indications: This product is only used for in vitro diagnosis. and it is for presumptive screening only and the need to consult a medical practitioner for confirmatory testing of positive results by a laboratory test and for follow-up clinical care.. Please read the instructions carefully before testing.

Additional Product description: The LabonaCheck™ A1c HbA1c Test kit is intended for the quantitative determination of glycated hemoglobin in human blood. The LabonaCheck™ A1c is a boronate affinity assay. The LabonaCheck™ A1c HbA1c Test kit consists of the cartridges, the R1/Reagent and the R2/Reagent. [EN]

The CERA-STAT™ 2000 HbA1c Test kit is intended for the quantitative determination gycated hemoglobin in human blood. It also provide the Estimated average glucose(eAG) value, in addition to the gycated hemoglobin result, allowing for easier diabetes care.
The CERA-STAT™ 2000 HbA1c Test kit is a boronate affinity assay. The CERA-STAT™ 2000 HbA1c Test kit consists of the cartridges, the R1/Reagent and the R2/Reagent.[EN]

CERA-STAT™ HbA1c Test Kit can quantitatively measure HbA1c measurements and eAG(Estimated average glucose) results using the boronic acid reaction with glycated hemoglobin (HbA1c) in the blood of the patients who are concerned about diabetes. Glycated hemoglobin (HbA1c) is the combination of hemoglobin molecules in red blood cells that carry oxygen with glucose in the blood. It indicates the ratio of the glucose concentration in the blood and reflects the average blood glucose level for 2 to 3 months. It is used as the most useful and accurate marker.[EN]

CERA-STAT™ CRP Test Kit can quantitatively measure the result of C-reactive protein (CRP) in the blood (whole blood, serum, and plasma) of the patients who are concerned with infection, tissue damage, inflammatory and chronic diseases using the immunometric assay and measurement principle. C-reactive protein (CRP) is a protein produced in the liver that is a biological marker that is sensitive to the rapid increase rate and degree of increase in acute inflammatory reactions and diseases such as inflammatory diseases or necrosis of body tissues. It is also known as a typical acute phase reactive proteins and provides information for the detection and evaluation of infectious diseases, tissue damage, inflammatory diseases and related diseases using it.[EN]

Name/Trade name(s): CERA-CHEK™ Hb Plus Hemoglobin Measuring System[EN]
Additional Product description: The CERA-CHEK™ Hb Plus Hemoglobin Measuring System is designed to help people measure the hemoglobin levels. Additional Product description: TICKPLEX® PLUS tests nodrošina kvantitatīvu un kvalitatīvu in vitro analīzi attiecībā uz cilvēka IgM un IgG antivielām pret vairākiem mikrobu izcelsmes antigēniem cilvēka serumā vai plazmā. Komplekts paredzēts, lai pārbaudītu Borrelia afzelii, Borrelia burgdorferi un Borrelia garinii infekcijas, un testi iekļauj dažādu borēlijas baktēriju persistentus antigēnus. Turklāt komplektu izmanto ar ērču pārnēsātajām slimībām saistīto poliinfekciju (Babesia microti, Bartonella henselae, Ehrlichia chaffeensis, Rickettsia akari) un oportūnistisko infekciju (enterovīruss, Epšteina-Barra vīruss, cilvēka parvovīruss B19, Mycoplasma fermentans un Mycoplasma pneumoniae) testēšanai. Šis komplekts ir paredzēts ērču pārnēsātu patogēnu infekciju diagnostikai. Testu komplekts ir paredzēts tikai profesionālai lietošanai klīniskās laboratorijas vidē, un to nedrīkst lietot paštestēšanai.[EN]

TICKPLEX® BASIC tests nodrošina kvantitatīvu un kvalitatīvu in vitro analīzi attiecībā uz cilvēka IgM un IgG antivielām pret vairākiem mikrobu izcelsmes antigēniem cilvēka serumā vai plazmā. Komplekts paredzēts, lai pārbaudītu Borrelia afzelii, Borrelia burgdorferi unBorrelia garinii infekcijas, un testi iekļauj dažādu borēlijas baktēriju persistentus antigēnus. Šis komplekts ir paredzēts ērču pārnēsātu patogēnu infekciju diagnostikai. Testu komplekts ir paredzēts tikai profesionālai lietošanai klīniskās laboratorijas vidē, un to nedrīkst lietot paštestēšanai.[EN]

Additional Product description:
The CanAg CA242 EIA kit is a manual enzyme immunometric assay intended for the quantitative determination of the cancer associated antigen CA242 in human serum.
The assay is indicated for use as an aid in the management of pancreatic cancer patients in conjunction with other clinical methods for monitoring pancreatic cancer.
[EN]

CanChek Tumor Marker Control Serum is intended for use as an assayed quality control serum to monitor the
accuracy of laboratory testing for Neuron Specific Enolase (NSE), S100B protein and Squamous Cell Carcinoma
Antigen (SCCA).[EN]

Fujirebio Diagnostics Tumor Marker Control is intended for use as a quantitative, assayed control serum to
monitor the procedures used in the laboratory for testing the analytes listed in the lot specific assigned values
sheet.[EN]

The CanAg CA19-9 EIA kit is a manual enzyme immunometric assay intended for the quantitative determination of the cancer associated antigen CA19-9 in human serum.
The assay is indicated for use as an aid in the management of pancreatic cancer patients in conjunction with other clinical methods for monitoring pancreatic cancer.
[EN]

The CanAg CA15-3 EIA is a manual enzyme immunometric assay intended for the quantitative determination of the cancer associated antigen MUC-1 (CA15-3) in human serum.
The assay is indicated for use in the measurement of CA 15-3 antigen to aid in the management of breast cancer patients. Serial testing for CA 15-3 antigen concentrations should be used in conjunction with other clinical methods for monitoring therapeutic measures in the management of breast cancer patients.
[EN]

The CYFRA 21-1 EIA kit is a manual assay intended for the quantitative determination of soluble cytokeratin 19 fragments in human serum. The assay is to be used as an aid in monitoring disease progression during the course of disease and treatment in lung cancer patients. Serial testing for patient CYFRA 21-1 assay values should be used in conjunction with other clinical methods used for monitoring lung cancer.[EN]

The CanAg ProGRP EIA kit is a manual immunoassay for the quantitative determination of ProGRP in serum. The CanAg ProGRP assay is to be used as an aid in the differential diagnosis of lung cancer and in the management of patients with small cell lung cancer in conjunction with other clinical methods.
The results must be interpreted in conjunction with other methods in accordance with standard clinical management guidelines.
[EN]

The CanAg PSA EIA is a manual enzyme immunometric assay intended for the quantitative determination of Total PSA (Prostate Specific Antigen) in human serum. The assay is indicated for the measurement of serum PSA in conjunction with digital rectal examination (DRE) as an aid in the detection of prostate cancer in men aged 50 years or older. Prostate biopsy is required for the diagnosis of cancer. This assay is further indicated for the serial measurement of PSA to aid in management of patients with prostate cancer.[EN]

The CanAg Free PSA EIA is a manual enzyme immunometric assay intended for the quantitative determination of Free PSA (Prostate Specific Antigen) in human serum.
The assay is indicated for measurement of Free PSA in conjunction with the CanAg (total) PSA assay to develop a ratio (% Free PSA) of Free PSA to Total PSA. This ratio is useful as an aid in distinguishing prostate cancer from benign disease in men age 50 years or older who have a digital rectal examination (DRE) that is not suspicious for prostate cancer and a CanAg total PSA value in the range 4 ng/mL to 10 ng/mL. Prostate biopsy is required for the diagnosis of
prostate cancer.
[EN]

The CanAg CA 125 EIA is a manual enzyme immunometric assay intended for the quantitative determination of the cancer associated antigen CA 125 in human serum.
The assay is indicated for use in the measurement of CA 125 antigen to aid in the management of ovarian cancer patients. Serial testing for CA 125 antigen concentrations should be used in conjunction with other clinical methods for monitoring ovarian cancer.
The assay is further intended to be used in conjunction with HE4 EIA as an aid in estimating the risk of epithelial ovarian cancer in premenopausal and postmenopausal women presenting with pelvic mass. The results must be interpreted in conjunction with other methods in accordance with standard clinical management guidelines.
[EN]

The CanAg CEA EIA is a manual enzyme immunometric assay for the quantitative determination of Carcinoembryonic Antigen (CEA) in human serum. 
This assay is to be used for serial measurement of CEA to aid in the management of cancer patients.  The results must be interpreted in conjunction with other methods in accordance with standard clinical management guidelines.
[EN]

The HE4 EIA is a manual enzyme immunometric assay for the quantitative determination of HE4 in human serum. 
The assay is to be used as an aid in monitoring response to therapy for patients with invasive epithelial ovarian cancer. Serial testing for patient HE4 assay values should be used in conjunction with other clinical methods used for monitoring ovarian cancer.
It is further intended to be used in conjunction with either ARCHITECT CA 125 II or CanAg CA125 EIA or Lumipulse G CA125II as an aid in estimating the risk of epithelial ovarian cancer in premenopausal and postmenopausal women presenting with pelvic mass. The results must be interpreted in conjunction with other methods in accordance with standard clinical management guidelines.
[EN]

The CanAg NSE EIA is a manual enzyme immunometric assay intended for the quantitative determination of Neuron-specific enolase (NSE) in human serum.
The assay is indicated as an aid in the monitoring of patients with malignant disease such as small cell lung carcinoma (SCLC) or neuroblastoma.

[EN]

The CanAg AFP EIA is a manual enzyme immunometric assay intended for the quantitative determination of α‑Fetoprotein (AFP) in human serum.
The assay is indicated for use as an aid in the diagnosis of hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC). The results must be interpreted in conjunction with other methods in accordance with standard clinical management guidelines.
[EN]

The CanAg S100 EIA kit is a manual enzyme immunometric assay for the quantitative determination of S100B (S100A1B+S100BB) in human serum. 
The assay is indicated for use as an aid in the management of patients with malignant melanoma. The results must be interpreted in conjunction with other methods in accordance with standard clinical management guidelines.
[EN]

The CanAg SCC EIA is a manual enzyme immunometric assay intended for the quantitative determination of squamous cell carcinoma (SCC) antigen in human serum.
The assay is indicated for use in the measurement of SCC antigen to aid in the management of patients with squamous cell carcinoma. Serial testing for SCC antigen concentrations should be used in conjunction with other clinical methods for monitoring disease progression in patients with squamous cell carcinoma.
[EN]

The Mesothelin Control is a lyophilized two level serum control for use as an assayed quality control serum to monitor the precision of laboratory testing procedures for soluble mesothelin related peptides (SMRP) with the Lumipulse Mesothelin assay.[EN]
The Lung Marker Control is a lyophilized two level serum control based on human serum containing the Cyfra, ProGRP, and SCC antigens.[EN]

The AMH Control is a lyophilized three level serum control
for use as an assayed quality control serum to monitor the
precision of laboratory testing procedures for Anti Mullerian
Hormone (AMH) with the Lumipulse AMH assay.[EN]

The CanAg Glypican-3 EIA is a manual enzyme immunometric assay for the quantitative determination of Glypican-3 in human serum. 
The assay is indicated for use as an aid in the diagnosis of hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC). The results must be interpreted in conjunction with other methods in accordance with standard clinical management guidelines.
[EN]

Additional Product description:
The test reagent devices consist of polystyrene microparticles as a solid phase carrier coated with
affinity binders, such as monoclonal or polyclonal antibodies. specific for the analyte (antigen), and
fluorescent affinity binder, such as monoclonal or polyclonal antibody, conjugates as a tracer. The immunoassay active components are dried with protective sugars and buffer components inside individual reaction chambers on test configuration packages.

The mariPOC® SARS-CoV-2 test reagent is intended to be used for the detection of SARS-CoV-2
antigens when there is a suspicion of acute upper or lower respiratory tract infection, or coronavirus
disease 2019 (COVID-19) caused by severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 (SARS-CoV-
2). The test reagent may be used for individuals with or without symptoms, in serial testing and in
monitoring to assess the contagious phase of the infection. The SARS-CoV-2 reagent detects
SARS-CoV-1 and SARS-CoV-2. The function of the device is for screening and/or aid to diagnosis
in order to provide specific information on the physiological state by providing limited information
on the microbiological content of the specimen. Intended specimen type is native (unprocessed)
nasopharyngeal swab or aspirate.
The use of the device is automated and the device is stored in dry format inside mariPOC® test plate
reaction wells. The results are reported qualitatively as positive (+) or negative (−) on the graphical
user interface of the mariPOC® Software.[EN]

Additional Product description: GlucoSure HT Blood Glucose Monitoring System is intended for quantitative measurement of glucose in fresh capillary whole blood taken from fingertips, palm, or forearm at specific points in time. It is designed for both home use by an individual and for use by healthcare professionals.[EN]

The UASure® Blood Uric Acid Monitoring System is intended for use outside the body (in vitro diagnostic use) in a clinical setting by healthcare professionals and at home by person with Hyperuricemia as an aid to monitor the effectiveness of the medication. The UASure Blood Uric Acid Monitoring System is not intended to diagnose Hyperuricemia or Gout, and results obtained from using the UASure Blood Uric Acid Monitoring System should not be use as a basis to alter medication without first consult a physician or healthcare professional.[EN]

The KETOSURE POC blood ketone monitoring system is intended to quantitatively measure blood ketone level in venous whole blood or fresh capillary whole blood drawn from fingertips.
The KETOSUR POC blood ketone monitoring system is intended for testing outside the body (in vitro diagnostic use). It is intended for use by healthcare professionals in laboratories such as physician office laboratories, clinics, and hospitals, as an aid in monitoring blood ketone level in diabetes mellitus. It is not indicated for diagnosis or screening of diabetes.[EN]

The MultiSure GK Blood Glucose and Ketone Monitoring System is intended to quantitatively measure blood glucose in fresh capillary whole blood drawn from fingertips, palm, or forearm, and blood ketone in venous whole blood or capillary whole blood from fingertips. Alternative site testing for glucose test should be performed only during steady-state (when glucose is not changing rapidly). Testing is done outside the body (In Vitro diagnostic use). The system is intended for selftesting by people with diabetes or for clinical settings by healthcare professionals, as an aid in monitoring blood glucose level and blood ketone level in diabetes mellitus. It is not indicated for diagnosis or screening of diabetes or for neonatal use.[EN]

Additional Product description: The BasePurifier™ 32 Nucleic Acid Extraction System 32 oscillating rods is a general laboratory device for automatic and simultaneous extraction and purification of nucleic acids from up to 32 samples, using extraction reagents comprising magnetic beads. Samples can be many different sources, like whole blood, cfDNA, ctDNA, cell colonies, solid biopsies, plants, soil, urine, feces, and others either purified directly or after some pre-treatment. The extracted and purified nucleic acids are suitable for polymerase chain reaction, gene-chip, gene hybridization, gene sequencing, cloning and other technologies, and can be applied to scientific research, clinical applications, food safety, forensic investigations, companion diagnostics, veterinary diagnostics, and other application fields. The instrument is intended for use by healthcare professionals or qualified laboratory personnel instructed and trained in the techniques of nucleic acid purification.[EN]

Additional Product description: EpiDirectTM MGMT Methylation qPCR Assay is a semi-automated real-time Polymerase Chain Reaction (PCR) assay intended for the direct, semi-quantitative analysis of the methylation status of the human gene of the DNA repair enzyme O6-methylguanine-DNA methyltransferase (MGMT). The assay is intended for purified genomic DNA (gDNA) samples that without further pre-treatment can be used with real-time PCR systems for the detection and quantification of the methylation status of MGMT. Samples comprise Formalin-Fixed Paraffin-Embedded (FFPE) and fresh frozen biopsies and can be prepared using automated platforms or in manual workflows. Methylation of MGMT is a prognostic and predictive marker in solid biopsies from glioblastoma patients. EpiDirectTM MGMT Methylation qPCR Assay is intended to detect and provide the relative quantity of the amount of methylated versus unmethylated DNA in the MGMT promoter. The assay is intended for use by health professionals or qualified laboratory personnel specifically instructed and trained in the techniques of Real-Time PCR as well as proficient in handling biological samples. Medical interventions based on results from this product requires medical authorization.[EN]

Additional Product description: SensiScreen® Liquid BRAF qPCR Assay is a semi-quantitative real-time Polymerase Chain Reaction (PCR) assay intended for the detection, identification, and relative quantification of specific somatic mutations in the human v-Raf murine sarcoma viral oncogene homolog B (BRAF) gene in cell-free DNA (cfDNA) purified from liquid biopsies including blood and plasma. The assay is used with real-time PCR systems and samples can be prepared using automated platforms or in manual workflows. The assay is an in vitro diagnostic medical device intended to aid in the detection, identification, monitoring of disease progression, and re-appearance based on BRAF mutation status. Additional Product description:
The TME Panel-1 clinical trial assay (CTA) is an investigational qualitative in vitro diagnostic assay that uses next generation sequencing (NGS) to determine a gene expression profile from formalin fixed paraffin embedded (FFPE) samples using the Illumina NextSeq platform. It is intended to be used as a predictive gene signature to determine the biomarker status of colorectal, ovarian and gastric cancer subjects that are candidates for enrollment onto clinical trials investigating the safety and efficacy of bavituximab or navicixizumab.
The assay is intended for laboratory professional use only, to be performed only at Almac Diagnostic Services’ Clinical Laboratory Improvement Amendments (CLIA)/College of American Pathology (CAP) accredited laboratory, 19 Seagoe Industrial Estate, Craigavon, United Kingdom.[EN]
